{{Unreferenced|date=April 2007}}

'''Dioptric correction''' is the expression for the adjustment of the [[optical instrument]] to the varying [[visual acuity]] of a person's [[Human eyes|eyes]]. It is the adjustment of one [[lens (optics)|lens]] to provide compatible [[focus (optics)|focus]] when the viewer's eyes have differing visual capabilities. One result is less strain on the eyes that allow for optimal viewing and [[depth perception|depth]] and [[contrast (vision)|contrast]] focusing when composing a [[photograph]] or viewing an item through a device made of lenses or lens elements.

