The first meeting of the '''Franco–British Nuclear Forum''' was held in Paris in November 2007, chaired by the Minister for Energy and the French Industry Minister. The working groups are focusing on specific areas for collaboration. A follow-up meeting on the issue in London was planned for March 2008,[https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debate/?id=2007-01-31a.228.6] but did not take place.[https://www.theyworkforyou.com/wrans/?id=2009-02-26a.255984.h]

